# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Blood of the World — Codex (local dev secrets, never committed)
#
# LEAVE BLANK to run the atlas fully offline against its bundled seed
# (src/lib/features/atlas/lib/seed.json). `npm run dev` works with zero backend.
#
# To point the atlas at the REAL Supabase project (after you've run the SQL in
# db/ — see README "Phase 0 step 3"), fill these from Supabase →
# Project Settings → API. The atlas data layer auto-detects: both present =>
# query Supabase; otherwise => in-memory mock. No code changes either way.
#
# For DEPLOYS (GitHub Actions), do NOT commit these. Put the same two values in
# the repo's Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions, named exactly
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY; the deploy workflow injects them
# at build time. This file stays committed as the template; .env.local stays
# gitignored. (§11.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# A real character_vessels row id to use as the test vessel, so the
# vessel_discoveries foreign key is valid. Offline mode ignores this.
VITE_TEST_VESSEL_ID=
